      638.44
    ],
    "text": "he appealed against the sentence and not against the order delivered on",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      645.56,
      527.52,
      659.56
    ],
    "text": "17.06.2022 by the learned High Court Judge in respect of the application",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      666.68,
      512.52,
      680.68
    ],
    "text": "made under 241(3) of the Code of Criminal Procedure Act No.15 of 1979.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      697.76,
      527.17,
      711.76
    ],
    "text": "In Sri Lanka, the period of time taken for a criminal appeal would depend on",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      719.0,
      527.02,
      733.0
    ],
    "text": "the court the original case was heard in and the court the appeal is being",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      740.14,
      506.28,
      754.14
    ],
    "text": "made to. The general time limits for the respective Courts are as follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      260.69,
      35.25,
      342.73,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0037/2023",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "4 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      88.32,
      527.03,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 From a Magistrate's Court to the High Court: The appeal must be filed",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      109.56,
      337.51,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "within 14 days of the date of judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      140.64,
      527.18,
      154.64
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 From a High Court exercising original criminal jurisdiction to the Court",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      161.76,
      527.02,
      175.76
    ],
    "text": "of Appeal: The appeal must be filed within 14 days of the date of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      182.88,
      233.57,
      196.88
    ],
    "text": "conviction/judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      214.08,
      527.14,
      228.08
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 Appeals by the Attorney-General: The time limit is generally longer,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      235.23,
      521.16,
      249.23
    ],
    "text": "such as 28 days for appeals from the Magistrate's Court or High Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      266.31,
      476.5,
      280.31
    ],
    "text": "In Rajapaksha v The State [2001] 2 SLR 161 the court held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      297.39,
      526.97,
      311.45
    ],
    "text": "(i) The journal entries indicate that the accused - appellant did not give any",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      318.51,
      526.7,
      332.57
    ],
    "text": "reasons for his absence from court and it was only then that the trial",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      339.75,
      526.77,
      353.81
    ],
    "text": "Judge had proceeded to enforce the sentence imposed on him on",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      360.87,
      526.95,
      374.93
    ],
    "text": "22.7.98 to be operative from 2.9.99. In terms of S. 241 (3) the accused",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      381.99,
      526.69,
      396.05
    ],
    "text": "person if he appears before Court and satisfies court that his absence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      403.13,
      526.72,
      417.19
    ],
    "text": "at the trial was bona fide, the court shall set aside the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      424.25,
      524.64,
      438.31
    ],
    "text": "conviction/sentence/order and the trial then would be fixed de - novo.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      445.37,
      526.68,
      459.43
    ],
    "text": "(ii) The essence of a judgment consists in the reason for conviction of",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      466.49,
      523.44,
      480.55
    ],
    "text": "acquittal of an accused person. The judgment in this case is a well-",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      487.61,
      257.69,
      501.67
    ],
    "text": "reasoned out judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      508.73,
      526.86,
      522.79
    ],
    "text": "(iii) The period of time within which an appeal should be preferred must be",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      529.85,
      526.72,
      543.91
    ],
    "text": "calculated from the date on which the reasons are given. The",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      550.97,
      526.75,
      565.03
    ],
    "text": "conviction/sentence was given on 22.7.98. The Petition of Appeal was",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      572.12,
      447.34,
      586.18
    ],
    "text": "lodged on 17.9.1999. The appeal is therefore out of time.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      593.24,
      526.8,
      607.3
    ],
    "text": "(iv) An application in Revision should not be entertained save in exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      614.48,
      526.81,
      628.54
    ],
    "text": "circumstances. When considering this issue court must necessarily have",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      635.6,
      526.68,
      649.66
    ],
    "text": "regard to the contumacious conduct of the accused in jumping bail and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      656.72,
      526.91,
      670.78
    ],
    "text": "thereafter his conduct in a manner to circumvent and subvert the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      677.84,
      526.8,
      691.9
    ],
    "text": "process of the law and judicial institutions. In addition, the party should",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      698.96,
      393.82,
      713.02
    ],
    "text": "come before Court without unreasonable delay.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      730.06,
      527.28,
      744.06
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Padmasiri v Attorney General 2012(1) SLR 24, it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      260.69,
      35.25,
      342.73,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0037/2023",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "5 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      88.32,
      526.84,
      102.38
    ],
    "text": "\u201c\u2026.if we are to allow this application it would amount to condescending",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      109.56,
      526.8,
      123.62
    ],
    "text": "or, the court lending its hands to a person who is guilty of contumacious",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      130.68,
      526.72,
      144.74
    ],
    "text": "conduct and thereby assisting him. Therefore, we hold that the petition",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      151.8,
      440.02,
      165.86
    ],
    "text": "of appeal is not properly constituted and is out of time.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      182.88,
      527.52,
      196.88
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Opatha Mudiyanselage Nimal Perera v Attorney-General",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      204.0,
      282.79,
      218.06
    ],
    "text": "[2002] 3 SLR 101 it was held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      235.23,
      526.68,
      249.29
    ],
    "text": "\"These matters must be considered in limine before the Court decides to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      256.35,
      526.9,
      270.41
    ],
    "text": "hear the accused-petitioner on the merits of his application. Before he could",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      277.47,
      526.68,
      291.53
    ],
    "text": "pass the gateway to relief his aforesaid contumacious conduct and his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      298.59,
      526.91,
      312.65
    ],
    "text": "unreasonable and undue delay in filing the application must be considered",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      319.71,
      526.68,
      333.77
    ],
    "text": "and determination made upon those matters before he is heard on the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      340.95,
      249.89,
      355.01
    ],
    "text": "merits of the application.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      372.03,
      527.28,
      386.03
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Attorney General v Podisingho 51 NLR 385, it was held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      403.13,
      526.69,
      417.19
    ],
    "text": "\u201cthe powers of revision of the Supreme Court are wide enough to embrace",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      424.25,
      526.66,
      438.31
    ],
    "text": "a case where an appeal lay but was not taken. In such a case, however,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      445.37,
      526.68,
      459.43
    ],
    "text": "an application in revision should not be entertained save in exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      466.49,
      526.88,
      480.55
    ],
    "text": "circumstances, such as, (a) where there has been a miscarriage of justice,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      487.61,
      526.82,
      501.67
    ],
    "text": "(6) where a strong case for the interference of the Supreme Court has been",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      508.73,
      526.63,
      522.79
    ],
    "text": "made out by the petitioner, or (c) where the applicant was unaware of the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      529.85,
      289.75,
      543.91
    ],
    "text": "order made by the Court of trial\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      561.08,
      524.28,
      575.08
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Ediriweera v Attorney-General (2006 1 SLR 25) it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      592.16,
      526.67,
      606.22
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIf the High Court Judge's order is correct, that there are no exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      613.28,
      526.69,
      627.34
    ],
    "text": "circumstances the order cannot be revised. Revisionary powers should be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      634.4,
      526.75,
      648.46
    ],
    "text": "exercised where a miscarriage of justice has occurred due to a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      655.52,
      526.94,
      669.58
    ],
    "text": "fundamental rule of procedure being violated, but only when a strong case",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      676.76,
      440.98,
      690.82
    ],
    "text": "is made out amounting to a positive miscarriage of justice.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      707.84,
      527.04,
      721.84
    ],
    "text": "In this case as stated earlier, the Appellant lodged an appeal against the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      728.98,
      527.0,
      742.98
    ],
    "text": "judgment. Considering the provisions of law, his appeal is out of time. He",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
